Awe c'mon George, I store all my dry cells in the freezer until needed because
the cold slows down the chemical break down. I stick the motorcycle batteries
in the garage refrigerator after a full charge to slow down plate
degeneration. Best of all world is a full charge and drain the acid, but that
is tough stuff to dispose of with all the regs around here!

